<p>This in and of itself is okay, but it is very strange considering that the code is basically 1 to 1, and pyFFTW always always calls itself an FFTW wrapper. It'd seem strange to me to include subtle normalizing factors with 0 mention.</p>
<p>Furthermore, I couldn't find <strong>anything</strong> about this online, searching stuff like &quot;pyFFTW scaling&quot; and &quot;FFTW vs pyFFTW different result&quot; etc, so this makes me worried that somehow I've made a mistake.</p>
<p>If someone has an explanation, I'd love to know.</p>

